On Mon, 27 May 2002, Dan Martin wrote:

> both shafts the same but does it make a diffrence which end goes to trans 
> axle

both ends of the shafts are the same BUT auto tranny shafts cannot be
switched side to side they are different lengths.
  as far as I know there is no difference which end of the shaft goes to
tranny or stub axle,  however it is usually reccomended that if you are
using old CV joints that these should turn in the same direction they did
before

